\|u\|_{2}\leq\|u_{0}\|_{2}+\int_{0}^{t}\|u_{t}(t,x)\|_{2}dt
\|u\|_{2}=\Big(\int_{\Omega}u^{2}dx\Big)^{1/2}
u_{0}=u(x,0)
u_{t}=\frac{\partial u}{\partial t}
\Omega
R^{n}
u=u(x,t)
u \in H^1(0, T; L^2(\Omega))
u(T) = u(0) + \int_0^T u_t(t) \, dt.
\| u(T) \|_{L^2(\Omega)} \le \| u(0)\|_{L^2(\Omega)} + \left\| \int_0^T u_t(t) \, dt\right\|_{L^2(\Omega)} \le \| u(0)\|_{L^2(\Omega)} + \int_0^T \| u_t(t) \|_{L^2(\Omega)} \, dt. 
